Hi there!

The document says [`SECURITY_UNAUTHORIZED_VIEW` defaults to `None`](https://pythonhosted.org/Flask-Security/configuration.html#urls-and-views), but actually it's default to [`lambda: None`](https://github.com/mattupstate/flask-security/blob/53c6547aff05f67712ff0bf2b388bbd62718000b/flask_security/core.py#L75).

```
def _get_unauthorized_view():
    view = utils.get_url(utils.config_value('UNAUTHORIZED_VIEW'))
    if view:
        if callable(view):
            view = view()
        else:
            try:
                view = url_for(view)
            except BuildError:
                view = None
        utils.do_flash(*utils.get_message('UNAUTHORIZED'))
        return redirect(view or request.referrer or '/')
    abort(403)
```

Since `lambda: None` is interpreted as true, by default `_get_unauthorized_view()` won't `abort(403)`, but the docs says it should.

